*exp*

(PHP 4, PHP 5, PHP 7, PHP 8)

exp â€” Calculates the exponent of e

===============================================================================
[ Description ]

  exp(float $num): float~

Returns e raised to the power of {num}.

  Note:

  'e' is the base of the natural system of logarithms, or approximately
  2.718282.

===============================================================================
[ Parameters ]

{num}

  The argument to process

===============================================================================
[ Return Values ]

'e' raised to the power of {num}

===============================================================================
[ Examples ]

Example #1 exp() example

<?php >
  echo exp(12) . "\n";
  echo exp(5.7);
<?>

The above example will output:

1.6275E+005
298.87

===============================================================================
